data.name: GraphicObjectShape
desc: This service is for a graphic shape.
**since**
LibreOffice 6.4

properties.name: AdjustBlue
desc: If this property is set, the blue channel of this graphic shape is adjusted by the given signed percent value.

properties.name: AdjustContrast
desc: If this property is set, the contrast of this graphic shape is adjusted by the given signed percent value.

properties.name: AdjustGreen
desc: If this property is set, the green channel of this graphic shape is adjusted by the given signed percent value.

properties.name: AdjustLuminance
desc: If this property is set, the luminance of this graphic shape is adjusted by the given signed percent value.

properties.name: AdjustRed
desc: If this property is set, the red channel of this graphic shape is adjusted by the given signed percent value.

properties.name: Gamma
desc: If this property is set, the gamma value of this graphic shape is adjusted by the given value.

properties.name: Graphic
desc: This is the graphic that represents this graphic shape.

properties.name: GraphicColorMode
desc: This property selects the color mode that is used for rendering.

properties.name: GraphicObjectFillBitmap
desc: This is the bitmap that represents this graphic shape.

properties.name: GraphicStreamURL
desc: This is a url to the stream (\"in document\" or linked graphic) for this graphic shape.

properties.name: GraphicURL
desc: This is a url to the source bitmap for this graphic shape.

Note the new behaviour since it was deprecated: This property can only be set and only external URLs are supported (no more vnd.sun.star.GraphicObject scheme). When a URL is set, then it will load the image and set the Graphic property.

properties.name: ImageMap
desc: This property contains an image map for this graphic.

properties.name: IsSignatureLine
desc: Whether this shape is actually a signature line.

properties.name: QRCodeProperties
desc: Shape as a QR Code.
**since**
LibreOffice 6.4

properties.name: SignatureLineCanAddComment
desc: Whether the user can attach a comment at signing time.

properties.name: SignatureLineId
desc: The ID of the signature line, used to connect to a signature.

properties.name: SignatureLineIsSigned
desc: Whether the signature line is signed using a digital signature.

properties.name: SignatureLineShowSignDate
desc: Whether the signing date should be shown in the shape.

properties.name: SignatureLineSigningInstructions
desc: Signing instructions, to be shown at signing time.

properties.name: SignatureLineSuggestedSignerEmail
desc: Suggested Signer Email.

properties.name: SignatureLineSuggestedSignerName
desc: Suggested Signer, Name of the Signer.

properties.name: SignatureLineSuggestedSignerTitle
desc: Suggested Signer, Line 2 (Title or additional information)

properties.name: SignatureLineUnsignedImage
desc: Image to be displayed when the signature line is unsigned.

Images for signed signature lines (valid and invalid) are to be retrieved via com.sun.star.security.DocumentSignatureInformation (you can get the matching signature with the SignatureLineId property).

properties.name: Transparency
desc: If this property is set, the transparency value of this graphic shape is adjusted by the given unsigned percent value.
100% is fully transparent, 0% is fully opaque.
